{
  "stem": "23942.6",
  "chunk_idx": 17,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When did it start to come back to you?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, it took me a long time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because till I learned, started learning-- when I came to America and I start learning Chumash.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it still didn't mean much to me because I still learn by rote.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, when I was introduced, I did it by rote.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I knew I must obey my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I knew I belonged-- my father's my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I saw him learning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I remember that my mother said my father was very learned in Torah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And suddenly, it dawned on me that I have to become who I-- who I am.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I didn't want to become-- that's when I realized I have to become who I am, who I was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and it, it took slowly, that it-- you felt it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- first, I did it by rote.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then, I, I start feeling it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, feelings and-- and doing are two different things, you see?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, so it slowly came back by stages.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Tell me, while you're, you're back at this Hanukkah part--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Hanukkah was very nice, celebrated beautifully.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was beautiful celebrated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what was exciting about Cracow was that all Jewish people came to Cracow from all parts of Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they realized they weren't safe in any of the smaller villages.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So everybody, even people from, from, from deep in Russia, when they came back, they went either back to Cracow, or they went to-- they went to Lodz, or to the largest cities because they knew they were safer there.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the villages were Judenrein after a while because they were killed by pogroms after the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Poles, there's no excuses.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
